  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0d82\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0db6\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0d85\u0d82\u0dc1\u0dba\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "If the corporation cannot, give it to the private sector",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister of Ports, Navigation and Aviation Mr. Nimal Siripala de Silva has advised the officials that if the Petroleum Corporation is unable to supply the necessary fuel for the planes, the import of the fuel should be given to a private sector party.",
        "A special discussion was held this morning under the chairmanship of the minister regarding the measures to be taken to re-establish the aircraft sector.",
        "The airlines that have joined this discussion have indicated that more flights will take place through Katunayake Airport especially in the coming months when the tourist season starts.",
        "They have also pointed out that continuous fueling of aircraft is essential."
      ],
